In a heavy skillet over high heat, bring to a boil the chicken broth, garlic, ginger and a pinch of black pepper. Add the salmon steaks, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 3 minutes. (If using fillets with the skin, start with the skin side up). Gently turn over the steaks and simmer another 4 minutes (covered). Remove the salmon to a platter. Cover and keep in a warm oven (150 degrees F max). Add the wine to the poaching liquids. Turn up the heat to medium-high and reduce the liquids to about 1/2 a cup, stirring frequently. Add the cream and reduce the heat to medium-low, whisking constantly until the sauce thickens (about 1-2 minutes). Add the chopped scallions and minced red bell pepper, stir. Taste test and add salt and pepper as desired. Return the salmon steaks to the skillet spoon the sauce over the steaks; reheating the salmon for 1-2 minutes. Serve.